# .joseph — Mission Canvas Workspace Debug & Reference
# This file contains everything Claude (or any AI assistant) needs to
# diagnose and fix connection issues with Joseph's workspace.
# Last updated: 2026-03-31

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# 1. ARCHITECTURE OVERVIEW
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# Joseph's workspace runs across two locations:
#
# VPS (always-on relay)         Joseph's Laptop (private)
# ├── server.mjs (:8787)       ├── git clone of pretendhome repo
# ├── joseph_bridge.py          ├── mcp_server_remote.mjs → calls VPS
# ├── monitor_daemon.py         ├── Claude Desktop / Cursor / Codex
# ├── cloudflared tunnel        ├── lens.yaml (PRIVATE — never upload)
# ├── workspaces/oil-investor/  └── local files (PRIVATE — never upload)
# └── Telegram bot polling
#
# All channels (MCP, Telegram, Web UI) talk to the SAME workspace
# data on the VPS. There is ONE source of truth.

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# 2. CONNECTION DETAILS
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

VPS_HOST=srv1390882.hstgr.cloud
VPS_IP=72.60.171.27
VPS_USER=root
VPS_SSH="ssh root@srv1390882.hstgr.cloud"
VPS_DIR=/root/fde/missioncanvas-site

# The VPS firewall blocks all ports except SSH (22).
# We use a Cloudflare tunnel to expose port 8787 externally.
# The tunnel URL CHANGES every time the tunnel service restarts.
# To get the current URL:
#   ssh root@srv1390882.hstgr.cloud 'journalctl -u mc-tunnel --no-pager | grep -oP "https://[a-z0-9-]+\.trycloudflare\.com" | tail -1'

# Current tunnel URL (will change on restart):
TUNNEL_URL=https://blake-flower-doctors-critical.trycloudflare.com

# Internal port (on VPS, not accessible from outside):
SERVER_PORT=8787

# Telegram bot:
TELEGRAM_BOT=@joseph_palette_bot
TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN=8748740444:AAE7mncPmZFZs45xxVgKAF1xMoFvDOxOBjQ

# Workspace:
WORKSPACE_ID=oil-investor

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# 3. SERVICES (systemd on VPS)
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# Four services run on the VPS:
#
# missioncanvas.service   — Node.js server on port 8787
# joseph-bridge.service   — Telegram bot (polls Telegram API, calls server)
# mc-monitors.service     — Background monitor daemon (Perplexity searches)
# mc-tunnel.service       — Cloudflare tunnel (exposes 8787 as HTTPS)
#
# All read env vars from: /root/fde/missioncanvas-site/joseph.env
# Python services use venv: /root/fde/venv/bin/python3

# Check all services:
#   ssh root@srv1390882.hstgr.cloud 'systemctl is-active missioncanvas joseph-bridge mc-monitors mc-tunnel'

# Restart everything:
#   ssh root@srv1390882.hstgr.cloud 'systemctl restart missioncanvas && sleep 2 && systemctl restart joseph-bridge mc-monitors mc-tunnel'

# View logs:
#   ssh root@srv1390882.hstgr.cloud 'journalctl -u missioncanvas --no-pager -n 30'
#   ssh root@srv1390882.hstgr.cloud 'journalctl -u joseph-bridge --no-pager -n 30'
#   ssh root@srv1390882.hstgr.cloud 'journalctl -u mc-monitors --no-pager -n 30'
#   ssh root@srv1390882.hstgr.cloud 'journalctl -u mc-tunnel --no-pager -n 30'

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# 4. COMMON ISSUES AND FIXES
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# ── Issue: Telegram bot not responding ──
# Cause 1: Bridge service crashed
#   Fix: ssh root@srv1390882.hstgr.cloud 'systemctl restart joseph-bridge'
#   Check: journalctl -u joseph-bridge --no-pager -n 20
#
# Cause 2: Server is down (bridge depends on it)
#   Fix: ssh root@srv1390882.hstgr.cloud 'systemctl restart missioncanvas && sleep 2 && systemctl restart joseph-bridge'
#
# Cause 3: Bot token revoked or another process is polling
#   Telegram allows only ONE polling process per bot token at a time.
#   If you run joseph_bridge.py locally AND on VPS, they will conflict.
#   Fix: Only run the bridge in ONE place. Kill the other:
#     pkill -f "python.*joseph_bridge"  (local)
#     ssh root@srv1390882.hstgr.cloud 'systemctl stop joseph-bridge'  (VPS)
#
# Cause 4: Bot not in group / privacy mode on
#   The bot must have Group Privacy OFF in BotFather settings.
#   BotFather → /mybots → @joseph_palette_bot → Bot Settings → Group Privacy → OFF
#   After changing, remove and re-add the bot to the group.

# ── Issue: MCP tools not working in Claude Desktop ──
# Cause 1: Tunnel URL changed (server restarted)
#   The free Cloudflare tunnel URL changes on every restart.
#   Fix: Get new URL and update Claude Desktop config:
#     ssh root@srv1390882.hstgr.cloud 'journalctl -u mc-tunnel --no-pager | grep -oP "https://[a-z0-9-]+\.trycloudflare\.com" | tail -1'
#   Then update MC_SERVER in claude_desktop_config.json and restart Claude Desktop.
#
# Cause 2: npm dependencies not installed
#   Fix: cd missioncanvas-site && npm install
#
# Cause 3: Wrong path in claude_desktop_config.json
#   The "cwd" must point to the missioncanvas-site directory.
#   On Mac: /Users/<username>/pretendhome/missioncanvas-site
#   Check: node mcp_server_remote.mjs oil-investor  (should not error immediately)
#
# Cause 4: Node.js not installed
#   Fix: brew install node  (Mac) or download from nodejs.org

# ── Issue: Web UI / tunnel not loading ──
# Cause 1: Tunnel crashed
#   Fix: ssh root@srv1390882.hstgr.cloud 'systemctl restart mc-tunnel'
#   Wait 5 seconds, then get new URL from logs.
#
# Cause 2: Server crashed
#   Fix: ssh root@srv1390882.hstgr.cloud 'systemctl restart missioncanvas && sleep 2 && systemctl restart mc-tunnel'
#
# Cause 3: URL is stale (changed after restart)
#   The tunnel URL changes every time mc-tunnel restarts. Get the new one:
#     ssh root@srv1390882.hstgr.cloud 'journalctl -u mc-tunnel --no-pager | grep -oP "https://[a-z0-9-]+\.trycloudflare\.com" | tail -1'

# ── Issue: Monitor alerts not showing ──
# Cause 1: Monitor daemon not running
#   Fix: ssh root@srv1390882.hstgr.cloud 'systemctl restart mc-monitors'
#
# Cause 2: Perplexity API key missing or invalid
#   Check: ssh root@srv1390882.hstgr.cloud 'grep PERPLEXITY /root/fde/missioncanvas-site/joseph.env'
#   Fix: Update the key in joseph.env and restart: systemctl restart mc-monitors
#
# Cause 3: Schedule hasn't elapsed
#   Energy markets: every 2 hours. AI investments: every 6 hours.
#   Check last run: look at monitors/*.yaml for last_run timestamp.

# ── Issue: "data_boundary blocked" error ──
# This is WORKING AS INTENDED. The server blocks personal data (emails,
# phone numbers, SSNs, credit cards, exact large dollar amounts from
# non-market sources). See DATA_BOUNDARY.md for full rules.
#   Fix: Rephrase without PII. Use ranges instead of exact amounts.
#   Example: "Position is in the $100K-250K range" instead of "$147,382"

# ── Issue: SSH to VPS fails ──
# Cause 1: SSH key not authorized
#   Fix: From a terminal that CAN connect, add the key:
#     echo "ssh-ed25519 AAAA..." >> ~/.ssh/authorized_keys
#
# Cause 2: Host key changed (VPS was rebuilt)
#   Fix: ssh-keyscan srv1390882.hstgr.cloud >> ~/.ssh/known_hosts

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# 5. LOCAL SETUP (Joseph's laptop)
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# Prerequisites:
#   - Node.js 18+ (brew install node)
#   - Git (brew install git)
#   - Claude Desktop or Cursor

# Clone:
#   git clone https://github.com/pretendhome/pretendhome.git
#   cd pretendhome/missioncanvas-site
#   npm install

# Claude Desktop config (Mac):
# File: ~/Library/Application Support/Claude/claude_desktop_config.json
#
# {
#   "mcpServers": {
#     "mission-canvas": {
#       "command": "node",
#       "args": ["mcp_server_remote.mjs", "oil-investor"],
#       "cwd": "/Users/<username>/pretendhome/missioncanvas-site",
#       "env": {
#         "MC_SERVER": "<TUNNEL_URL from section 2>"
#       }
#     }
#   }
# }
#
# After editing, restart Claude Desktop completely (Cmd+Q, reopen).

# Cursor config:
# File: .cursor/mcp.json in the project root
#
# Same format as Claude Desktop config above.

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# 6. MCP TOOLS AVAILABLE
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# workspace_brief    — daily brief (health, blockers, nudges)
# ask                — ask anything about the workspace
# resolve_evidence   — resolve a missing evidence gap
# add_fact           — add a known fact (PII-checked)
# verify_mastery     — confirm understanding of a concept
# list_gaps          — list missing evidence
# list_decisions     — list open decisions
# workspace_health   — health score breakdown

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# 7. TELEGRAM COMMANDS
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# /start           — welcome + command list
# /brief           — executive daily brief
# /gaps            — evidence gaps & blockers
# /decisions       — open decisions
# /health          — health score
# /research <q>    — Perplexity research (live web search)
# /alerts          — recent monitor alerts
# /monitors        — active monitors and status
# /resolve ID text — resolve an evidence gap
# /fact text | src — add a known fact
# /workspace id    — switch workspace
# /workspaces      — list all workspaces
# /help            — command list
#
# Free text: Smart-routed — research questions go to Perplexity,
# workspace questions go through the convergence chain.

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# 8. DATA BOUNDARY (CRITICAL — READ THIS)
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# The VPS NEVER stores personal data. This is enforced in code.
# See DATA_BOUNDARY.md for the full Tier 1 immutable policy.
#
# BLOCKED (server rejects these):
#   - Email addresses, phone numbers, SSNs
#   - Credit card numbers, bank accounts
#   - Street addresses, dates of birth
#   - Exact large dollar amounts (from non-market sources)
#
# ALLOWED:
#   - Abstract descriptions ("upstream-heavy exposure")
#   - Market data ("WTI at $97/bbl" — public data)
#   - Industry/domain labels
#   - Risk posture, investment horizon
#
# Joseph's private files (deal memos, portfolios, financials)
# stay on his laptop. Claude reads them locally via MCP.
# Only sanitized, abstract facts go to the VPS.

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
